The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Lin Dan thrills home crowd
                                                                                                                       7                                      Lin Dan thrills home crowd
                      
	Guangzhou: Kimiko Date Krumms 40-year-old legs finally gave out on her Sunday at the Asian Games.         
	Date Krumm, the Japanese veteran who returned to the WTA Tour in 2008 after a 12-year break, lost 7-6 (6), 3-6, 6-2 in the semi-finals to Chinas Peng Shuai.         
	It ended the No. 1-seeded Date Krumms attempt to win Asian Games gold medals 16 years apart, her first having come in front of her home fans in 1994 at Hiroshima.         
	Peng will play Akgul Amanmuradova of Uzbekistan in the gold medal final.         
	In the mens badminton final, Beijing Olympic champion Lin Dan of China beat world No. 1 Lee Chong Wei of Malaysia 21-13, 15-21, 21-10. Lin thrilled a packed house at the Tianhe Gymnasium, particularly when he clinched the win with a hard smash to the open court, took off his shirt, threw it into the crowd and then saluted two sides of the stadium.         
	World champion Nicol David won her third Asian Games squash gold with a 3-1 victory over Au Wing Chi of Hong Kong.           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                 
